{
  "stem": "13096.1",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the Allies were trying, you know, to-- to put down all the ships, and they were coming to, you know, to bombard them at night or during the day.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But as, you know, a millimeter of-- of mistake in the air, you know, the bomb, instead-- many of them instead of falling on the-- on the ship, they were falling into the Juderia.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It means that many people, Jewish people were killed.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the first one of this bombardment happened on Yom Purim and everybody was in shul and the whole half of the Juderia was destroyed.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So after that-- after that, so fearing for our lives, we went and live in the villages because the villages are far away from the port and everybody tried, you know, to hire a little house or to rent a little room or whatever it is, and we went there.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So that's why we were away, you know, from Rhodes Island when the German came later on, to find us.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Did any people try to leave Rhodes Island, Jewish people?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, that is between '38 and '44, the time when we left the island.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So first of all they were trying to go by their own means, you know, with boats and whatever they can find, you know, to go to Turkey.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Other ones, they were even hiding in small boats owned by Turkish and Greek people to go to Anatolia, which is the nearest part of Turkey, nearest part to-- to Rhodes Island.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So and-- and then it happened also in 1940, a big boat carrying about 1,500 refugees from Eastern Europe, they were leaving for Israel.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So it happened that when they were in the vicinity of the waters of Rhodes Island, it burned.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
